    The Variantset resource is provided so that an app can access variants within a vcf file. It is useful for querying the variance of a particular chromosomal region and for different genome broswers to find the variance in a particular location. Variants are extracted from VCF files and stored in a document database to enable fast range-based queries. There are two parts: the "variant set", which contains the information in the VCF file header, and the "variants", or the data lines in the VCF file.
